product.title: Multinautic 5 ft. x 10 ft. Medium Freeboard Aluminum Floating Dock Kit Model QPF-495 Without Cedar Decking
product.description: This page presents the 5 ft. x 10 ft. Medium Freeboard Aluminum Floating Dock Kit Model QPF-495 without Cedar Decking, product 21568. With its medium freeboard of roughly 16 in. above water, you will easily board a boat from this dock. With the Multinautic QPF-495 Aluminum Dock Series, reaching out to your dream of a dock that fits your needs is easy. This simple Collection lets you combine 5 ft. x 10 ft. dock sections in a straight line, side by side or in an ''L'' shape to adjust to your design. It's the perfect dock size unit for a light frame assembly that offers a low or a medium freeboard depending on your favorite nautical activities and the specifications of your shoreline. Simply choose Stationary and/or Floating Ensembles with or without Cedar Decking. Each unit is modular, letting you decide of the exact configuration that will suit your precise needs. The combination of 3 or more dock sections in a basic Floating layout (stationary plus semi-floating plus floating) allows you to moor a boat of up to 25 ft. long. Its sleek and unique designed aluminum frame system allows you to insert your mooring cleats (and other accessories) in the top track, without drilling into your decking and relocate them where you want. Decking boards can be assembled as panels to be rapidly removed from the sub frame to lighten manipulations year after year. The included assembly hardware for the frame is all stainless steel or hot dip galvanized.
feature_bullets: Stainless steel assembly hardware for a durable dock
descriptive_attributes: To help you decide what combination is best for your waterfront, look at the short installation planning guide. More details can also be found in the assembly guide. Both files are available from this web page. The basics are also described below

Floating dock system must include a semi-floating ramp that you will create with a floating kit, before your semi-floating ramp, install enough stationary docks to reach further out to the floating area in up to 4 ft. of water depth

To create your floating dock layout, transform 1-floating dock kit into a semi-floating dock using only 2 of the 3 supplied floats, switch the 3rd float to a second floating dock for a total of 4, all following dock sections will have 3 floats each

Medium freeboard floating dock unit comes with three 24 in. L x 60 in. W x 12 in. H foam filled dock floats, with 500 lbs. of buoyancy each, long hexagonal bolts with super-sized flat washers are included for their safe installation

Floating dock needs anchor chains to stay in place this dock kit includes a pair of chain hooks download the assembly and installation guide for details and to evaluate your specific needs anchoring materials will be purchased in your area

Exact size of this aluminum frame structure is 60 in. x 116 in. x 6.5 in. it includes a pair of hinges that can be installed on the short or the long side, multiple-units dock can be made to create a U shape that will protect your boat from strong waves

Manufactured in the United States by Hendren Plastics, Eagle Floats exceed all the marine industry standards for encapsulated dock flotation using cutting edge technology: infrared telemetry - computer controlled streaming

Suggested lumber for this kit is cedar for its lightweight, and its natural protection against mold and insects do not require any coating, thus keeping water free from chemicals, smooth on bare feet. (Cedar decking kit 21178)

Use the junction stabilizers to join 2 floating docks sections that will not bend at junction on a straight layout or to make a stable 10 ft. x 10 ft. platform at the end of the dock system and even create a separate swimming raft for the kids
Aluminum is not suitable for salt water
